rComments: Great class! There were 3 quizzes, but each of them had a study guide (same with the exam) so it was actually possible to do well.  The election paper and the book review are straightforward--all around good class!!
Great Professor. You don't need to attend every class. She puts on the notes on handouts, if you miss a class she passes out old handouts every class period. Really sweet lady.
Most of the information she puts on online copies of her lecture.  Pretty easy class - she only tested us on the basics.
Imformative class, I learned most everything on my own. Notes are onlnie which is very useful.  Read the book before tests and you will be fine.

I took comparative politics with her for one semester.  Overall, the class was very dull.  I would often fall asleep during lectures because the information was highly disorganized.  She kept online notes which was a +, but during lecture she was just unbearable to listen to.
